The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Treaty to empower women
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Treaty to empower women
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Oct. 13: India, Brazil and South Africa are set to joins hands to battle discrimination against women.         
	The countries  the bloc is known as Ibsa  are scheduled to sign a memorandum of understanding for co-operation on gender equality at the end of a two-day conference that started here today.         
	Women in each of the three countries face some common problems and some specific problems. We can learn from each other in dealing with both sets of problems, a senior official of the women and child development ministry said.         
	Last October, the three countries had set up an Ibsa womens forum  an idea backed by UPA chairperson Sonia Gandhi, sources said.         
	The MoU will give a backbone to our verbal understanding on how to co-operate to improve the condition of women, the official said.        
	Government sources said the three countries had agreed on the MoU.                                                                                                                                                                          
